{
  "stem": "5275.3",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "This was really very marvelous [SIGHS] until-- [PAUSES FOR 12 SECONDS] [DRINKS] July 11 [PAUSES FOR 7 SECONDS] in 1944, 3 and the wife of the director called me in and gave me a letter from my mother.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[CRYING] My mother said she was arrested.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "She was in prison.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They found out that the person she had papers for was dead, so she told them her real name.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "She told me not to try to look her up or see her, because too dangerous.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 7 SECONDS] [CRYING] She told me that I should remember what she always taught me, that the world belongs to the brave.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I should be brave.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "[DRINKS] [CRYING] It will be difficult for me, but [SIGHS] she wrote to her friend with whom she was working in an office in Krakow, and she told her what to do-- namely-- again, she found somebody in the prison who, for money, would smuggle a letter.",
      "word_count": 47
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And she wrote a letter to that friend to what to do.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And last night I translated it.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "This is the letter that-- this is a Xerox of that letter which she wrote.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "I don't know where she found this paper in the prison.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "I don't know where she found the pen.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "It's amazing.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "But again, she spoke German, and as you see from the letter, she immediately was offered a job in the prison by the Germans as a translator.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "The name of the friend of hers was Krisia.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "She said, 'Dear Krisia, I am on Montelupich.' Montelupich was a German prison in Krakow. 'I will be going to Plaszow'-- Plaszow was the other prison where we were for two weeks before-- 'or will be staying here and will be working in the office.",
      "word_count": 45
    }
  ],
